Approach 4: HashSet (Optimal)
Intuition

Store every element in a HashSet.

Only begin counting if the current number is the start of a sequence.

A number is the start when

num - 1

does not exist.

Then keep checking

num + 1

until the sequence ends.

Each sequence is visited only once.

Java
class Solution {
    public int longestConsecutive(int[] nums) {

        Set<Integer> set = new HashSet<>();

        for (int num : nums) {
            set.add(num);
        }

        int longest = 0;

        for (int num : set) {

            if (!set.contains(num - 1)) {

                int currentNum = num;
                int currentStreak = 1;

                while (set.contains(currentNum + 1)) {
                    currentNum++;
                    currentStreak++;
                }

                longest = Math.max(longest, currentStreak);
            }
        }

        return longest;
    }
}
